title: Spring Daleans bag top positions in shooting tournament
text:
AMRISTAR: Spring Dale Senior School bagged top positions in the School District Shooting Tournament held here on Saturday. Nabarun Singh Sidhu, from Spring Dales, bagged the first position in the under-19 boys' category in the Air Rifle event, while Sehnazdeep Singh Sandhu and Harsuhail Singh, both Spring Daleans, bagged the second and third positions in this event.
In the under-19 Girls' Air Rifle event, Penaz Heir, of Spring Dales, bagged the first position, while Kavya Jain, also from Spring Dales, won the second position. In the under-17 Boys' Air Rifle category, shooters from Spring Dales including Shehbaaz Singh Gill, Dhananjay Dhammi, and Mohammed Bilal Farooqui, won the first, second and third positions, respectively.
Sanya Khanna and Shivpreet Pannu, both from Spring Dales, were first and second, respectively, in the Under-17 Girls' Air Rifle event. Ashmit Singh and Sumant Khanna, also Spring Daleans, bagged the first and second positions, respectively, in the under-14 Girls' Air Rifle event.
Meanwhile, Dhanush Bhalla and Mohammed Owais Farooqui, both shooters from Spring Dale Senior School, won the first and second positions, respectively, in the under-17 Boys' Air Pistol event.
